{'id': 11694579, 'body': "Hi Elvite - Thank you for providing feedback on BPme Rewards. We very much value your business and hope to keep you as a loyal consumer. We are sorry that you are unhappy with the new BPme Rewards program. We take your feedback seriously and will continue to look for ways to improve the experience for our best consumers. BP continues to review support for additional payment options and will continue to work towards expanding payment options through BPme.

If you'd like to send us a private message (consumer@bp.com), we will do our best to assist you further. 

Thank you, BP", 'modified': '2019-11-06T16:30:00Z'}

{'id': 11740278, 'body': 'Hi Brianpumper_jr. - We are sorry to hear about your experience. I want to make sure you are aware that if you would like to participate in the new program, you need to download the new BPme mobile app from the Apple or Google Play and create a new account. 

If you have already done this, we would love to look into your login and connecting payment card issues. You can contact our support team at 1-800-333-3991 and they will do their best to assist you further.

Thanks, BP', 'modified': '2019-11-08T19:19:24Z'}

{'id': 12212418, 'body': 'Hi ilovegirls516 - Thank you for providing feedback on BPme Rewards. We very much value your business and hope to keep you as a loyal consumer. 

BP and Amoco sites are independently owned and operated and set their own prices, including terms for different payment methods. When using the BPme app to purchase fuel, you will always be charged the stated credit card price. To receive any other prices (debit card pricing or discounts for specific credit card brands) that are offered by the stations, you cannot use the BPme app. Rather, you must use your actual linked payment card at the station. Any qualifying purchases will be counted in BPme Rewards.

Thank you, BPme Rewards Team', 'modified': '2019-12-04T16:15:07Z'}

{'id': 12714599, 'body': 'Hi Regnarts, For security reasons, cards will be removed from your BPme mobile wallet due to a few different reasons. 

If you log out from the app, if you sign into your account using a new phone, or if you have not signed into your BPme account for 90 days, the cards will be removed and will need to be added back in again to use mobile payment from the account. 

To prevent cards from being removed, you can stay logged into your account, and just close the app when you are finished. This will retain all of your card information for your next fuel purchase. You will need to log-in each time with either your Pin/Touch ID or Face ID, but your card and account information will all be retained. Thanks, BPme Team', 'modified': '2020-01-03T21:39:40Z'}

